reviews.text:
Restaurant is on the second floor above the Axis luxury apartments leasing office. Stairs and elevator available but the entrance was not well marked from the outside. Tons of seating indoors and outdoors on their patio with a lot of tables, padded seating, and tons of space.

We got the panini chicken, black burger, and chipotle burrito. ~$40 total. Not really worth it.

The black burgers bun was very dense and the patty didn‚Äôt have much flavor. The fries were pretty good but nothing special. We got the panini half chicken and half steak which was awesome that they did that for us. The steak side was way better than the chicken side that was a little dry and flavorless. The chipotle burrito wasn‚Äôt the best and even after bringing it home for leftovers it wasn‚Äôt finished and ended up in the trash.

I think the positive reviews may be skewed since it‚Äôs in a college place, or the menu items we tried were just bland that day.

Our visit to Fresko had us hopeful, given its high reviews. The restaurant's cozy ambiance and welcoming staff set the stage for what we anticipated to be a delightful evening. However, our excitement quickly dissipated once our meals arrived. Despite the restaurant's high ratings, the food failed to impress. My request for a well-done burger without tomatoes was overlooked, resulting in a practically rare patty with unwanted toppings. The burger was so poorly cooked that it had a jelly-like consistency, and it was so bad that I had to spit it out. Adding to the disappointment, my girlfriend's ribs were cold. It's puzzling how the online reviews could have been so off the mark with this place. While the atmosphere and service were commendable, the lackluster food left us very disappointed that we just spent $40 for a bad meal.

I'm so happy I found this lovely restaurant! The lighting, decor and music created an enchanting atmosphere! The people who work here are so incredibly nice and give high quality service!
I got the salmon, and it was perfect! Every savory bite melts in your mouth! And the salad that comes with the meal complemented the salmon! Also, the water here tastes great!
Thank you Fresko, for making my evening so much better! I can't wait to come back and try something else on the menu! :)

The food here is AMAZING! My sister and I went here to see how it was and we have very specific diets. The Fresko salad was SO good and I didn‚Äôt feel like shit after eating it. A small business, but a great one. Definitely check it out if you are hungry and in the area. The dude that works there is super helpful too.

This place was great! The look and feel of the restaurant, the food, and the service were all great! Our waiter was super friendly and genuine! We got the salmon and the black burger, both of which were excellent! We definitely plan to go here again!
